    {
      "type": "text", "id": "footer_01",
      "x": 160, "y": 800, "width": 1240, "height": 80,
      "text": "Systemd boundary:    all 3 services managed via systemctl   ->   journalctl -u <svc> -f    for logs\nIngress only on :80 + :443 + LiveKit RTC ports (UFW). All inter-service traffic is loopback (127.0.0.1).\nNo database, no redis, no message queue. State lives in memory; persistence is the secret files + the systemd unit definitions.",
      "originalText": "Systemd boundary:    all 3 services managed via systemctl   ->   journalctl -u <svc> -f    for logs\nIngress only on :80 + :443 + LiveKit RTC ports (UFW). All inter-service traffic is loopback (127.0.0.1).\nNo database, no redis, no message queue. State lives in memory; persistence is the secret files + the systemd unit definitions.",
      "fontSize": 12, "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top",
